    {
      "charEnd": 1010,
      "charStart": 322,
      "factId": "hz.web.6a53e3b2f5b03b87.fact.2",
      "kind": "bullet",
      "text": "Quick Links GITHUB HOME FULL DOCUMENTATION REPORT A PROBLEM Getting Started To use OmniAuth in a project with a Gemfile, just add each of the strategies you want to use individually: gem &lsquo;omniauth-github&rsquo; gem &lsquo;omniauth-openid&rsquo; Now you can use the OmniAuth::Builder Rack middleware to build up your list of OmniAuth strategies for use in your application: use OmniAuth::Builder do provider :github, ENV[&lsquo;GITHUB_KEY&rsquo;], ENV[&lsquo;GITHUB_SECRET&rsquo;] provider :openid, :store =&gt; OpenID::Store::Filesystem.new(&lsquo;/tmp&rsquo;) end By default, OmniAuth will return auth information to the path /auth/:provider/callback inside the Rack environment.",
